{
  "answer": "**I could not find a couplet by Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq (in *Diwan-E-Zauq*) that matches this description.**\n\nThe corpus contains the full *Diwan-E-Zauq* (60 ghazals/chapters in English translation). Searches across the English bodies for phrases like \"breath\" + \"complaint\" + \"flame\"/\"fire\" + \"heart\", or variants (\"sigh\" for *nafas*/*naala*, \"complaint\" for *shikayat*, etc.), yielded no results in Zauq's work.[^1]\n\nRelated motifs appear elsewhere:\n- Ghazal 39 compares a suppressed *naala* (sigh/complaint) to smoke rising from an inner fire.[^2]\n- Ghazal 28 warns against *shikayaton* (complaints), but without breath/flame imagery.[^3]\n\nIf this refers to a specific couplet by its Urdu phrasing (e.g., *nafas-e-shikayat* as *shola bar dil*), it may not align exactly with the English translation, or it could be from another source. The Falsafa corpus covers 37 works; classical Urdu poetry is limited to Zauq, Ghalib, and Iqbal here. Let me know more details for further checks!  \n\n[^1]: Multiple `search_corpus` queries (e.g., `\"breath\" \"complaint\" \"flame\" \"heart\"`, `\"sigh\" \"flame\" \"heart\"`, etc.) returned 0 hits for Zauq.\n\n[^2]: *Diwan-E-Zauq*, ch. 39 (*Na karta zabt main naala to phir aisa dhuaan hota*), [p-1b63cf](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/39-na-karta-zabt-main-naala-to-phir-aisa-dhuaan-hota/translation/#p-1b63cf).\n\n[^3]: *Diwan-E-Zauq*, ch. 28 (*Khoob roka shikayaton se mujhe*), [full chapter](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/28-khoob-roka-shikayaton-se-mujhe/translation/).",
